Not being able to move forward on my goals can create hardship because I can handle other aspects of my life independently, not so much with technology. With Godaddy, I never worry about that; just like 911, there is always someone there ready to walk me through what I need to do to get me back on track. The value of this simple customer service step can not be stressed enough. I also feel like the Godaddy staff are lovely and patient and make all efforts to figure out how they can help me. My experience over the last 12+ years with them has not been perfect (nothing ever is) but knowing that they are a call away from solving my technical issue is the difference between me succeeding. I am always going to be grateful to the staff at Godaddy!!

title: The WORST hosting/registrar company out there
text: Please please STAY AWAY from GoDaddy. I'm actually sad at the amount of ads I see on TV and other places for their services—and how many people get trapped into their plans. Not only have I seen ridiculous prices in the past for what's included in the plans, but their server speed and WordPress performance is TERRIBLE. I've been a web designer for 7+ years, and GoDaddy has singlehandedly been the absolute worst and slowest host to deal with.  My clients have constantly had issues pop up with their WordPress website, and it's extremely annoying that they ban certain plugins from getting installed to your website. For example, you can't install most backup, caching, and security WordPress plugins due to "compatibility" issues with their network. (I've never seen this issue with other hosts.)  Not only this, but their support system is awful. Though they have some friendly representatives, it's extremely hard to get a hold of them. Most times I've reached out to them, I was put on a 30-minute hold, and usually the request goes through many people before they even get to it. The live chat function doesn't work. The "texting" SMS support never gets back to me. Do yourself a favor and stay FAR away!

I have spent, by no exaggeration, hours on the phone and on your online chats trying to sort out issues your company has caused for out business, which is yet another cost to us. title: Don't be fooled. You'll have access to TRIAL site builder when buying a domain
text: The process to get your domain is straightforward. What is not is the wording and marketing about what you get when you sign with GoDaddy. By the time this review is being written, the wording on their ads and website is that by buying a domain with them you have access to their website builder (save that word, "access"). When you do have your configuration set and ready to go prior to adding things to the cart, one of the options read "Start building your website for FREE" yes, with capital letters, and yes, save that term "Start building" Although this is not considered a lie, this is just misleading.  When you're shopping domains, you'll face several companies trying their best to lure customers in. The way GoDaddy is doing this is to avoid at any costs to mention the word TRIAL. That's when the marketing department is working hand-to-hand with the legal department to avoid being sued. Getting back to the terms used: When they say in their ads that buying a domain will give you access to their website builder, they're not lying. You'll have access to it. When they say you can start building your website for FREE, they're not lying, you'll START (that's the word that should be in caps) building the website. However, all that is just the marketing to lure you in and add things to your cart. Once the payment is processed and you receive the thank you message, you'll have access to your dashboard. Only then, you'll see that the access you have to the website builder is just the trial. The same trial you would have if you were just curious about knowing how this tool actually performs. But what now? You already bought the domain. Yes,  I know you can cancel the purchase if you want. But that's not the point. GoDaddy should tell their customers that the access they're getting IS a trial and they'll have to SPEND more money to MAINTAIN their website. There is NO promotion to this, there is NO advantage to this. All you have is a trial period to build your website and once that's gone and you need to maintain it, you'll have to pay for it. Again, this is NOT a complaint about the technicalities of the tool. this is a complaint about how this is worded to lure customers into thinking that GoDaddy is going above and beyond the competition giving a toolset to customers that other companies don't. which is clearly not the case.

title: From Hell to Heaven
text: My experience with GoDaddy in the past has always been amazing. HOWEVER, post COVID true service has left and the days of "The Customer is Always Right" have left. In-fact, last week I waited on the phone to speak to a customer service person regarding a tech challenge that was causing my website to fail and labeling it as an UNSAFE WEBSITE. I was concerned and willing to wait the 90 minutes it took to hear a human voice. The person answering seemed nice and listened for a very short time and said:  "I will be right back." I was placed on hold. I waited for another 90 minutes. Then, YEP, disconnected!  SDF! It is challenging to find that kind of time, however important, especially when the challenge is not resolved. Today I had time and called GoDaddy. Mr Highland answered my call. He allowed me, an unskilled computer user that knows what I want and ZERO idea of the words to use or the understanding to completely explain my challenge. He listened, repeated, listened and then explained the challenge. He helped me with the google reseller account. (such a complicated situation) He changed the settings on the GoDaddy side and then helped me with getting the right information in the right location. He then helped me with another GoDaddy account providing my Customer number and how to find my PIN. I was so happy at the end of our time, nearly 90 minutes, I find myself glad the first person made me wait for 90 minutes just so I could speak to Mr, Highland. Almost..  A BIG Thank you to Mr. B Highland!! GREAT JOB

title: Abuse of Authority and/or *DOS?
text: I migrated a law firm’s web site from GoDaddy to a new provider. Its uptime was at 100% for months.  Suddenly, the site became unreachable because the domain’s registrar, GoDaddy, inserted a record into the DNS table. The record redirected the site’s IP address and prevented clients and the general public from accessing the site. The altered IP address is  listed in the AbuseIPDB and pointed to a GoDaddy advertisement where the site’s domain was offered for purchase; further tarnishing the law firm’s reputation and highlighting an abuse of authority by GoDaddy.   *Denial of Service (DOS)

title: WARNING: Never Search for a Domain on GoDaddy
text: WARNING: Never Search for a Domain on GoDaddy to buy!!!! Read on.... I searched for a domain to see if it was available at the official UK registrar Nominet The domain I wanted was available So assumed I could buy it for less than £10. Off I went to GoDaddy to purchase this domain as I use them to manage and host a few small websites. Searching for it on GoDaddy and it says the domain is unavailable. However GoDaddy informed me that they could obtain the domain for me using their "Broker Service" for just £51.99. But I knew the domain was available, so I went to another registrar and bought it for £5. Wow GoDaddy, want a 1000% markup on that domain!! So either  1) GoDaddy's system to check domain availability is fundamentally flawed and returns incorrect results. or 2) They are deceitfully showing domains as registered to get the £50+ fee.....  For a company this size it is shocking either way. I wonder if this breaches any of their agreements with Nominet

title: A website is more than just a static location on the internet - it's a personal thing...
text: A website is more than just a static location on the internet - it's a personal thing - whether it's for a business, product, service, or organization... or just for someone to have to showcase their own creations. In our automated world of today, setting up a website can be a simple one-step process, but it can also be quite complex when migrating an existing site and redirecting additional domain addresses into a new website - with individual emails and a link to a third-party shopping cart. If not familiar with the inner workings of such a process, the exercise could prove more than just a mental strain if not for the help of the support staff at GoDaddy.   "Sharon" - The person I just had the pleasure of working with - was exceedingly patient, and helped me mitigate what could have been a nightmare of a project! With her kind guidance, the new website will soon be up and running, and we'll be sleeping like a baby tonight! Thank you, Sharon!!

title: Total Scam - AVOID
text: I signed up for the free trial to create a simple website, easy enough. East to use platform though doesn't have the editing/formatting choices of WIX (my previous supplier). But it looked good for £5.99 a month. The sales are VERY PUSHY, when you ask for advice they repeatedly ask "Shall I set that up for you" taking no time to understand your needs and offering prices far beyond those advertised. Interestingly if you want a discounted 3 or 5 year deal you CANNOT do this after your trial, you HAVE TO CREATE THE WEBSITE AGAIN FROM SCRATCH! Yes seriously, from scratch.  There is something very wrong about this company, I don't believe that they can have so many great reviews when the experience has been so awful. I'm deleting my account, writing off the time I invested in the trial, and grateful that I didn't sign up/commit before realising their misleading practices.

title: I am very disappointed that our domain…
text: I am very disappointed that our domain name was suspended due to a detected piece of malware which was inserted by one of our users.  I understand the need to protect against such cyber security issues, but to do so in this way, with no more than 24 hours' notice over a holiday period is poor. A better way would be to redirect the A record in question to a parking page until the issue can be resolved which would avoid the propagation time and give the customer an opportunity to self-manage the issue. We have a large number of customers all around the world who are currently denied services. Lack of appreciation for this fact shows very little empathy for the challenging commercial climate all customers currently operate under. More of an effort should have been made to contact the customer about the matter and a faster process to unsuspend the domain is needed given the time it takes to re-propagate the DNS rules. GoDaddy needs to offer differentiated services for its Enterprise customers and its SME customers.

This happened in November. 2. They were supposed to have done that move in March 2022 when I renewed. I found this out when I called mid november becasue I drop down menu they fixed stopped working. The customer service rep told me that there was a mistake and I should have been moved over. She said that I would have to revert back to the March site (why I do not understand). I agreed, I just wanted it fixed.  From there, it was a nightmare and then entire site crashed and when fixed I had to manually redo the edits I had done since march. 3. I had a clone site on c Panel (as recent as November) and thought I could use that to get back the edits and copy and paste. Well, that clone, I was informed, had been compromised and did not work anymore..... 4. My theme is outdated so I need a new one. When I tried to do a staging site, GoDaddy had never deleted an old url and the site keeps redirecting to it. Still waiting for this to be fixed 5. You are at the mercy of the rep. They always, no matter what, route you to the salespeople. If they cannot sell you anything, you get transferred. Then, more than likely, that person is wrong and you get transferred again. 6. My average call time with them is 1 hour or more. Since these issues in November, I have spent nearly 10 HOURS talking to someone and being on hold.  Here I am, over a month in the half making with lost revenue and time and still no solution.

title: Godaddy STOLE my domain name.
text: Godaddy STOLE my domain name. So having 100’s of domain names over the years I understand the process, I have all my domains on auto renewal and any domains I do not want auto renewal on I switch off, yet still get email after email informing me the domain is about to expire etc.  That is until you have a domain that you purchase for over $4000. I ended up not using the domain and putting it for sale in their platform. I then get a representative contact me saying they have an offer for the domain which I accept, 3 days later the domain is removed from my account of which I thought nothing of as a price has been agreed. I was informed the money would be in my account within 7 days. After waiting 4 weeks and after having numerous conversations with the broker that sold it, informing me his support team were trying to reach me to ask me to transfer the domain (did not receive one call or email from them) I then chase again to be informed that the domain had expired days before the broker contacted me asking if I want to sell it! i did not receive ONE email from them stating the domain was due to expire and to top it all off it was on AUTO RENEWAL.  So they have just stolen my domain and sold it, I have the emails to prove it, I have emails stating they had received funds and would send to me 7 days after the domain had been transferred!  Absolute scam of a company, there are many places to buy domains so I would suggest dealing with a company that will not steal your domain and sell it behind your back. They have zero support either so trying to get hold of them is almost impossible.

title: Bittersweet best describes GoDaddy
text: A 5 star feedback but marred by a very disappointing 'pricing' experience to renew a domain name, that which I registered with GD in 2020. The 5 star feedback is specifically for the customer service staff at GD, particularly two key representatives who I engaged with via telephone. Gianira, the first and subsequently Ron. Absolutely excellent contact with these two fine people and easily contacted without delay or issue. Gianira especially called me back on numerous occasions to help sort things out....now the bad news...having registered a new domain name for my existing business, I paid a nominal first year registration fee. Having faith and trust in GD, I left the option for 'auto renewal' on. A year after I was horrified to see a registration renewal fee had been taken for £180. Immediately contacted GD, inform that my chosen domain was a 'high level' one, attracting the rather expensive renewal cost. News to me! I was advised to call up GD, a week or so prior to the next year renewal, to discuss the cost and pretty sure an arrangement could be made. Year two, I did just that and despite every effort made by Gianira and her 'so called' Supervisors, no reduction whatsoever was offered on the £150 + VAT, not a single penny. Frustrated and disappointed by this, I scoured the market for competitive renewal quotes and lo and behold, 123-reg renewed the domain name, for one year at the miserly fee of £22.99 + vat. What A Difference! In conclusion...Go Daddy...you have the ABSOLUTE BEST Customer Service Staff ANY company could wish for... but you seriously need to review AND amend certain Domain Registration renewal fees, otherwise you'll lose clients such as I, once we realise how we're being conned and lied to. It is ONLY due to the efforts, honesty, understanding and integrity, of Gianira and Ron, at GD, that I will remain as a customer for hosting/e-mail, otherwise, I'd not hesitate to offer my business elsewhere.  G.D.... Got to Do better!

title: Extremely Overpriced
text: GoDaddy charges £74.99 for SSL certificates which you can get for free with Let's Encrypt. They do not add anything of value compared to Let's Encrypt certificates (which some hosting companies offer completely for free, including automatic renewal). On top of that, GoDaddy won't let me revoke a certificate after I canceled the product (even though I still have the certificate, full certificate chain, and private key). Customer support is OK over the phone, although they don't always answer during opening hours. Apart from that, there are no other channels. No email support, no ticket system, no live chat -- yes, GoDaddy advertises 24/7 live chat but IT DOES NOT WORK. I have tried multiple times with the latest Safari (v16) and Firefox (v108) over the past 6 weeks and the chat just won't load. This isn't "world class" or "award winning" customer support by any stretch of the imagination! GoDaddy's account centre / control panel where you manage your products is also slow and clunky. And GoDaddy upsells you expensive addons like "Website Security Basic" and "Ultimate Domain Protection" when you buy domain names. Again, some of the benefits included are offered free with other providers. I know this because I had a family member buy a domain name, who isn't tech savvy (that was a mistake!). He ended up paying £££'s for addons which were never used (particularly "Website Security Basic" which requires a setup procedure) before I helped him transfer to another registrar. Oh and their .com domain names are more than twice as expensive to boot as when you buy from other registrars! In conclusion, GoDaddy is overpriced and difficult to reach for support. That said, THEIR CORE SERVICES DO WORK RELIABLY and they offer a decent amount of options for them, so GoDaddy could be a good choice for the rich & technically inept. However, for personal and small businesses, I see no reason to choose GoDaddy for domains or SSL over better (less well known) alternatives.

title: Go Daddy is a seriously unscrupulous con company
text: Go Daddy is a seriously unscrupulous company, they ransom your web address back to you if you miss your renewal, the ransom slowly increases the longer you don’t pay Do not use them, I cannot believe they can get away with such criminal methods. Thanks for the reply Go Daddy but you haven’t contacted me to try and resolve this. So I will explain here: The first scam was to put the website up on auction, you have to sign up to a subscription to even bid on it which costs £20 a month (I claimed it back from PayPal) at which point Go Daddy had automatically put in a bid at the same time they secured the .co.uk equivalent name so I couldn’t switch. they must write In algorithms to bid you up to there valuation, in my case was £780 for an obscure name. Then they offer a service to buy back the site from the new owner which is of course go Daddy, that will cost £51.99 they call it a broker service fee. All this money going out and you still haven’t got your own web address back. Even if you pay all this money you don’t know how much there going to charge you and to top it off there will be a 20% commission . it’s disgusting!

title: Unauthorized Renewal
text: I have a website that is little visited but wanted to keep.  Got my renewal notice from GoDaddy and found a different provider (MochaHost) much cheaper which would suit my needs. So I switched. Meanwhile received 2 emails (12/10/22 and 12/20/22) saying they could not auto renew since my cc expired in 2020, and I needed to update it.  As I was not planning to stay with GoDaddy I didn’t update the info.  Today I received notification that a 2 year renewal for >$200 had been processed, when they never had the updated cc info.    I called and got them to refund the charge but what a POOR business practice. Added after Reply below from GoDaddy Tom - thank you for the info.  If I had known that I would have called to cancel.  Instead I received the following email from GoDaddy, which certainly implies the account will NOT continue without updating my info. Your payment method isn't valid. Maybe your payment info isn't complete or your card expired. Whatever the reason, sign in to your account and take care of this today. Update Payment Now    Economy Linux Hosting with cPanel Renewal - 12/30/2022 Hurry though. If you wait too long your products will expire and stop working — and any services connected to them will also quit. While you're at it, add a backup payment method to further protect your products and avoid any hassle

title: I've been a GoDaddy customer since 2015…
text: I've been a GoDaddy customer since 2015 and spent over 20.000 USD with them. I've never had issues with them (besides their ridiculous high prices) until recently. 4 days ago, I received an email from GoDaddy with a request to remove a single page on my website within 24 hours (insanely short timeframe for a page on an inactive domain/website) since it "violates their TOS". I did not read the email on time and my account got suspended. I contacted support, explained my store, the friendly lady on the phone gave me temporary access to my cPanel again to delete the single page that is against the TOS. (Not adult, no DMCA content, nothing weird, just a simple registration page) After deleting the page, I noticed the domain (worth about 1.500 USD) was deleted entirely from my account/possession. The friendly lady on the phone went after the issue & informed me after about an hour of calling that I had to send an email because this matter was beyond her control. After sending an email, i received a reply from GoDaddy's "Digital Crime Unit" informing me my service is suspended and I will not regain possession of my expensive domain name without any elaboration why. (a.k.a my domain is stolen by GoDaddy) Their email:  "Hello, The referenced product has been permanently closed. The product will be made unavailable permanently. Our decision is based on our compliance requirements and internal policies, which direct that permanently closed products are not eligible for reinstatement, and is not intended as an accusation or derogatory claim. Regards, Digital Crimes Unit" When asking for elaboration, I receive the same email over & over.  Shortly summarized: Amazing white collar scam GoDaddy. This company knows no loyalty nor ethics. 90% of hosting companies offer better prices and support & the best thing is, they won't steal your property without any elaboration.

title: Raymond was a terrific representative
text: Raymond was a terrific representative. He was a delight to deal with. Was informative and took care of my issue. The only improvement to the phone assistance, would be eliminating the digital assistant and replacing them with real people. Psychologically, when a person has a problem with a product, digital operators increase the frustration and anger. Having been a phone receptionist, a live person can dilute an angry caller by simply stating a long greeting. Example: “Hello, GoDaddy.com. This is “name of operator” How may I direct your call?” A long greeting deflates their intense emotion. People upset are ready with a challenging attitude. Waiting through a digital voice, and menus, intensifies the anger into a verbal abuse mode. Something to consider for the betterment of customer experience. It could also be a selling point for your products. People would choose GoDaddy products first, for banning digital operators.

title: Don't subscribe to their service
text: I can write a 3 page essay on the horrendous policies and services of this company in the last 1 year.  I have my domain registered with Godaddy and use 2 Unlimited Business Email plans in Workspace email since quite a few years. Last year, I paid for the renewal of my email plans for 2 years, not knowing that they are going to phase out the product. So, 1. I should have received an email about it 2. They sent us an email saying we will be 'auto-migrated' to the new Microsoft 365 email plan soon. 3. This did not happen till Dec, 2022, and during every followup we were told 'it would happen soon'. #Falsepromises 4. During this period from April 2022- Dec 2022, we faced A LOT of issues with Workspace Webmail. For each and every unique problem, the only thing the Guides would tell us after their SOPs (change password, use incognito mode) was that the problem is at our end. REALLY? All my other emails (Gmail, Ymail etc) and websites etc. work fine, only Godaddy is the issue, but yes I should change my Internet provider. Right. 5. In Dec 2022, this started impacting my business badly. It is our busy season, and we cannot login to our mails, there are issues with sending/receiving, and the Guides tell me. that Workspace is at End of life so they cannot help. 6. So I suggested that they give me credits for the unused amount on my already paid email plan, which I can use to upgrade to Microsoft plans. They refused. I asked for help to backup my webmail to whichever other provider I choose. They refused. THANK YOU SO MUCH. I dont know which award they won for customer service, but the "talk to our award winning guides" ad is not genuine.

title: AVOID these two - Varun K and Alekhya Y.
text: Worst customer service experience. I got an email saying that my products would get renewed and I needed to update my payment method.  I contacted them because I needed help updating my payment methods (and I want the service to continue). While speaking with them, I connected to Alekhya Y. I asked this person if I renew it for longer, I could get discounts, and the madness started.  1. Alekhya said yes, and sent me an offer to renew it for three years (with no discount). I said to Alekhya that there was no discount, and it was impossible for Alekhya to understand that the price was the same as renewing it every year (Alekhya kept saying that there was a discount - granted as a loyal customer - but there was none) 2. in the meantime, I saw that my plan was called Microsoft 365, so I asked if I had access to it. Alekhya said I had, but I tried downloading it but couldn't without upgrading. 3. Alekhya sent me a link that I used to select another email plan (with a discount!), but that meant doing a backup and having a new email.  I kindly asked Alekhya to pass me on to someone else; it was getting messy. Alekhya ignored my ask three times, trying to "solve" the confusion. I finally got passed to Varun K (a supervisor), to whom I complained about Alekhya and his answer was: "Yeah, I'm reviewing the conversation." After the answer, I asked: Do I have a Microsoft package? Alekhya said I had; he said, "It is active," and suddenly, Alekhya was back answering the questions. I asked Alekhya what had happened to Varun? That I need to speak with someone else. Alekhya connected me back to.. guess who? VARUN! I asked Varun why he left, and he was, "Was facing some issues." and with the worst attitude on the planet. I asked him why Alekhya and himself were saying I have a Microsoft package. His answer was: "was referring to email essential plan.." which was not my question! I started the chat at 10:34 am, it is 1:26 pm, and I am still trying to figure out a way to complain about Varun. Because I asked him to whom I could complain about him, and his answer was: "I think there was a misunderstanding" This is a joke; please, someone from GoDaddy contact me. I am more than happy to send you the whole conversation for you to see the poor service that both Alekhya Y and Varun K deliver.

I spoke with GoDaddy tech support and they confirmed that it was an issue they were aware of and their developers were looking into it, however they did not offer any compensation to help me as people were visiting my website and being redirected to adult sites! They offered me discount on future renewals but this was useless to me as I had only just purchased the hosting so I was at least a year away from renewal. Terrible hosting and disgusting that is was redirecting a family-friendly website to adult content. Please think twice before using GoDaddy and look at smaller businesses for hosting and other trusted ones.

title: Do not trust them with your company!!!
text: I have been a customer of GoDaddy hosting and domain services for almost 18 years. I have never had an issue with their customer support or anything up until a few years ago. I noticed that they no longer have US side support and from then every time I called things were not always as easy to get help as it had been.  I have been trying to get support help for the last 4 days to fix the server access that has redirected my website domain to a porn site. This is causing me several thousands of dollars of lost work and possibly future clients and damages.  I have spoken with managers Dj and John Jorden and both were not able to get it fixed. This has happened repetitively over the last 4 days and I have several videos showing proof of the issue that I have shared with the IT support teams. Nothing has been done to fix it. Tickets are opened but nothing has been done. I have been told to reply with more information but there is no way to do this. I will add more information to my review.  It has now been almost a week that every website on my GoDaddy server is getting redirected to a porn website. Today at times it only redirects to porn other times to a fake site for windows defender.  I have now spent over 8 hours on hold in the last week and spoken with Dustin, John Jordan, DJ, David, and Claudia.  At this time it has been confirmed that it has nothing to do with the code on my website and is a known problem with GoDaddy servers also. I have video proof in a sharable one drive folder for anyone that wants it.   Ticket ID: 16711448763924 Ticket ID: 16711446153229 As of today, this will most likely cost me several thousand dollars in lost income, time, and credibility. Updated 1/10/23 So after almost 2 weeks of my websites getting redirected to porn sites GoDaddy finally fixed the issue with the server redirect. I was also told that my code had nothing to do with it and it was handled with GoDaddy on the whole shared server. No apology no discount for the 2 weeks I had clients and contract offers redirecting to porn destroying my reputation. Just closed out the tickets and that's it. I have to wonder if I didn't spend almost 30 hours on the phone for that 2 weeks if they would have ever fixed it? I am very disappointed in the way this issue was handled.

title: They are liars
text: They are liars. They emailed me and said my card declined (thank goodness) when they tried to charge me $191 for my basic website even though (as I was told by their representative that the basic plan is $143.  I told them I have never been charged that amount of money and I said no to the charge.  Then I see a charge for $263 for a premium website! I never wanted their premium service. Have never had their premium service. I don't need their premium service. I have tried on numerous occasions to get my money back from them. First they said they would send me $120 back to equal the price of the basic service which the rep said was $143 (again, not $191). When that never happened I contacted them again. They said they gave me a store credit to which I said ABSOLUTELY NOT! Why would I want a credit for this lying, deceitful company. Then (in the same conversation) they said they were trying to refund the money to my bank but the bank was refusing it. (Another lie). I called my bank when I was on the chat with Godaddy. The bank has never seen any transactions coming in from them. Then they said they would "mail me a check". Seriously!! I am going to cancel my service as soon as I can and I hope enough people read this to make a difference in the way this company conducts business. It's appalling. Retraction issued on 12/16/2022-Since this review has been written, I heard from the manager of online reviews. He asked me to reach out to him so we communicate on this issue directly. Based on the information I provided he refunded the entire $263 (I only asked for $120 which would have made the price correct for the Basic Plan). He also renewed my account for one year.  GoDaddy stepped up to the plate and did the right thing so I will retract my previous review. I will say one thing. I hate writing bad reviews. You really have to push me to my limit to get me to write one. It would have been nice to be able to resolve this without going to this legnth. But I appreciate their willingness to work this out and I will continue to host my website with GoDaddy.

title: unbelievable decline in service by godaddy
text: Wow; after having been a loyal GoDaddy customer for years--decades, even--because they had earned it with quick response times to questions and excellent support--after being on hold now for 30 minutes (phone) and being in an unanswere chat for 20 minutes--I'll include here what I've written to read to the phone person or write to the chat person, IF I'm ever able to get in touch with anyone: "It is WAY TOO LATE to "exceed my expectations"; this opportunity was lost after the first 2 minutes of being on hold on the phone, and being told that my "estimated wait time" in the chat was 9 minutes... and then 5 minutes later being told that my "estimated wait time" was TEN minutes.  Really??  This is NOT the kind of service I have come to expect from the last DECADES OF MY LOYAL PATRONAGE.  Whatever you're doing, it's a result of incredibly poor planning.  Even other than that, I'm not having a good day RE: godaddy: my "notification" of changes to the e-mail system consisted of me (a) not being able to access my email, (b) not being able to change the password, (c) discovering that you're trying to pawn me off on to Microsoft 365 (the entire principle of which I am opposed, AND I refuse to have anything to do with Outlook, because IT SUCKS), and (d? e? what letter am I up to now?) a 40-MINUTE WAIT for godaddy phone support? I need to get my e-mail access back (temporarily--because if today is any indication of godaddy's current direction, my next move--after MANY YEARS of being a GoDaddy customer, both personally and on behalf of my business--is to find another service provider).  :( :( :(  Please help me get access to my e-mail!!!!! very unhappily, -pt" P.S. - After 40 minutes on hold (and about 20 minutes waiting for a chat response), I finally did get in touch with GoDaddy tech support.  They had, in fact, sent out e-mails warning us of an impending e-mail system change (which--for whatever reason--I hadn't seen), but that's really irrelevant (except that had I seen them, I would, in fact, have known that the change was going to occur).  And--as usual--when I did finally get in touch with someone, they (Kurt) were very competent and helpful.  However, my comments about planning and the decision they made about the platform to which they moved--AND FOR WHICH WE ARE NOW BEING CHARGED EXTRA!!--still stand.   I-can-get-to-my-email-now but still very-unhappy, -pt

title: 'Sold' what I didn't want. Management refused to cancel order or credit account.
text: I called GoDaddy to discuss moving my email hosting. I described my company and how we use all Google tools including Google business email, Chrome, Google Pixel phones, etc. I mentioned that my goal was to avoid Microsoft products. The sales person told me how great they are and sounded smart. I bought the package they suggested and moved my domain from Wix. After the transfer, it turns out that Microsoft is the service GoDaddy sells; the salesperson simply didn't mention it. There was an hour wait when I called during business hours, so I used chat and got a manager, Kawalpreet K. He said there was nothing he could do. He could not even credit the account the $140 for getting me into this mess. The salesperson, Rick, didn't return my emails. My domain is locked at GoDaddy for 60 days and then I have to move it back and pay a fee for doing so. I'm glad to know how they operate. I thought they had good service, like Amazon for example, but I was wrong. They will tell you what you want to hear to get the sale and then try to get you to stay with them or keep your money if you got tricked into the wrong package or product. They could do better by not selling a service they know the prospect doesn't want or need. They could do better by taking responsibility and acting ethically.  It's unfortunate that the company cares more about tricking someone out of $140 than their long term reputation. UPDATE - On 12/30/2022 I was issued a partial refund of $50 after Tom, GoDaddy Online Customer Reviews, contacted me. He was very professional and reasonable. I changed my Review from 1 star to 2 for this reason.

title: GoDaddy service deteriorates significantly
text: I am a long time customer of GoDaddy (more than 20 years). Service had always been great until 3 months ago when I noticed a suspicious charge notification email from GoDaddy. I tried to login to see what the charge was all about. But I can't. The 2-step authentication said it sent me the code, but didn't. I can receive text from other service providers such as Google and all my friends. I am now locked out of my account for 3 months. The support call wait queue is averaged now at 20+ minutes. I called in, after listening music for almost half an hour, the support person told me that they were experiencing texting service issues these days. The support person can't even tell me anything about the charge since he cannot authenticate me (hello, I am calling from the phone # on file!!).  The only thing I can do is to remove the 2-step authentication. In order to do that, I must follow a link to upload a copy of my driver license, so I did. About more than a week later, I received an email asking me to email the copy of my driver license, so I did. Today, after a month later after that, I have not heard anything back from GoDaddy. I am wondering what is going on there. I am now at a cross point of moving away from GoDaddy to somewhere else. I will update later when I have a resolution. UPDATED on 12/14/2022 - I finally received an email yesterday with a link to reset my password and was able to login back in to my account. I was not able to login to my account for a month. Luckily I did not have any deadline to deal with during that time. But I was really worried. I am still wondering why can't GoDaddy use my registered email address as identity verification. Instead, they had me go through three rounds of driver license upload, the last round had to be my face along with driver license. I felt like a prisoner checking in to prison:( 12/15/2022: Response to GoDaddy's response - I appreciate your feedback and you are serious about protecting my privacy and confidentiality of my account for which I just upgraded one star to two. But I have an email address on file, can't your system simply send me a verification code by my email for which I have used for more than 20 years!!

title: The worst in the planet by far
text: The worst in the planet by far,  super unethical and unprofessional people, DO NOT fall for this. It is a LOOP, a TRAP I say. once you start subscription. so BEWARE , to say NO to GoDaddy.   just cause they get a Capt.Dhoni and other celebs to advertise with some cools ads mean they have the visibility but they are terrible Web Host and their customer service simply sucks...even in the most polite conversation with the call centre executive online, they leave the chat abruptly and the system sends another executive and they have a patent dialogue, "SORRY FOR THE INCONVENIENCE, we are here to help you ." and then with good faith I start again explaining my plight and after a 8-10 mins he/she is also gone in thin air, just disappear and this goes on forever more... here is a case in point they have been hosting me for over 9 years...They lure people on with their fancy offers and once you are sucked into the trap next year onwards they renewals plans etc. takes the pulp out of you when there are cheaper and better options out there but you are compelled to pay up the extra sum for the sake of peace of mind. and linger on with GoDaddy for another year and then another year and you are simply stuck in a loop, a TRAP.  Then you wish to migrate the domain and go with another web host like Hostinger or SiteGround etc.  but you can not move your domain even after your domain is expired.  it is expired means it is available for the public to buy the domain if they wish to, anybody can but nah GoDaddy will park the domain with them for a period of 1 year , in short you can not migrate to any one else as the domain is still with GoDaddy post the expiry of the domain.  can you believe the scam, in short we are stuck with GoDaddy yet again, helplessly, they say it is with the domain Registry and guess what when you further probe on the 'Registry' and look deeper and further by visiting the webwhois.verisign to check who is the domain registry with , and am told the domain Registry is with GoDaddy but they encroach on your property to blackmail you further as you have no choice but to continue to RENEW with them, but they weird part is that they blame the 'registry' and we get fooled. and when probed further you realise every web-hosting company has their own registry and so GoDaddy keeps your domain and refuses to release it to us (post expiry) so they in short know that you will give them any bucks to retain your domain by paying the extra bucks. or it could go to someone else. cheap tacts right ? 'all in the name of safety', hahaaaa...bloody hell.  super unethical and unprofessional people do everything in their capacity to paralyse you.  so you are compelled to give into their soft demands.  Then they tell me it is taken by some other customer, imagine in a span of 1 hour they changed the story thrice and now they tell me it is bought by some Domain Agent -  and his commission to release the space is 5328/- for one year, this is  including his commission, can you imagine the layer of stories and the tricks they play to keep the customer with them by hook or crook.  and to my utter dismay I learned the Domain agent is also one of them. I mean internal team / department that blocks the expired website in order to make the client desperate to pay the additional price to keep their business and domain intact.  this is the next level of strategies they apply and do we have a choice , actually not right ?  well almost everybody will give in but I chose to lose and negotiate with another domain after much tryst.  but the long and short of it that they do everything they can in their capacity to keep the client hooked to them and even if that means they have to sell their soul , they will do that as well. and sure they have done the same in my case. shoddy immoral practices.  Karma is for real and that day is not far. when they pay the price.

title: Auto Renew ON Scam w/ NO OFF w/o FEAR from Go Daddy…
text: Update 12/15/22 - wish I found trust pilots go daddy page a LOT sooner because this was solved by GoDaddy within days after I posted this and I am grateful to Joe M. at GoDaddy | Manager- Online Consumer Reviews Dept and encouraged him to extend my complaint to the higher ups so these fear based alerts they send us all freaking stops. I hope we all keep complaining if we want it to change. Thank you Jo at GD and thank you TrustPilot for being an outlet for us. In 2020 my webmaster and I transferred hosting to Go Daddy because I was quoted a rate by "Chris" we were told would be honored at our 2-year renewal. Anytime you start anything with Go Daddy they activate auto-renewal "saying" you can shut that off at anytime & to that I say lolol. A month before hosting would auto renew the emails all caps began saying I will loose my website/URGENT/ and one of the worst GD scams where they say they tried (why I don't know) to charge my cc and its not valid or expired so "HURRY before its too late!" They kept sending those emails about a hosting due to renew in 6 weeks. I don't even THINK they said it was for "hosting." They just scare the hell out of you with repeated high drama, red letters, all caps, & bolded letters. BUT never include facts or info: not including their email is about a domain or hosting and I guess...if hosting ends your domain name is at risk? That was insinuated in their latest email saying I could LOOSE my website. 6wks of GD emails while I am checking MY responsible adult notes and ical alerts that warn me 2WKS before (due to GD tactics TO freak out customers & they literally do NOT care lol) and being it is now an appropriate week away from being due & the close of my first 2yrs I wanted to check they'd honor their quote. I am a novice & DG obviously created their company modo's for people like me. I looked an hour and could not find the amount of money they were planning on charging me to renew. If I "fixed my cc on file" first GD would just charge the amount they want! I still didn't know why GD "tried to charge my cc" or what could be wrong with my cc they just charged in July? FYI- my bank said GD did not attempt a charge recently(lol). After 40 mins waiting on a text w/ GD who say it's "quick" I gave up and actually didn't sit on hold on the phone very long at all! I spoke to Stella #4675 at GD who confirmed a few key things: 1. until you "check"off the product to renew and click "add to cart you can not see what GD will charge you lol. 2. conveniently because, & someone is super slimy to come up with these MANY small, seemingly little hiccups meant to pursued us to give up and be deflated, you can NOT "add a product to the cart" from a mobile device lol. So, they keep bringing you back to "update your cc" hoping you'll give up and update your card so they can charge you. For many who only have smart phones, you're screwed. That moment I only had my phone so Stella added it to my cart for me and instructed I would now be able to see GD's price to renew.wow. 3. GD had ZERO intentions of keeping their word (yes I know, stupid me) and they would have charged me TRIPLE their quote - without notice, without informing me of the increase in black and white- without anything BUT the fear based emails, the warnings I'll loose everything because my cc is not working. GD do not email customers FACTS like your REAL renewal date or the cc on file w/ the last four digits in order to push you to their site. Those many emails ALSO do NOT include THE COST of your renewal or if its 1 or 2-yrs. They do NOT give customers options on their website from within your account to assign & agree how far ahead we would like to receive their threats of fear aka "reminder emails." If fixing this were real for GD THAT would solve complaints I'm reading online. That's as far as I'll take my 1,2,3 but if you've dealt with GD you're aware it goes up to 11. I also found that SSL alert in C-Panel many others complain about where they say it's been self assigned and something went wrong and then the UPGRADE button is mysteriously more visible. For a novice it looks as if your websites not working since "January 2022" (suddenly GD had no need to send email warnings?) Forgetting THAT for now, I need to SHUT OFF AUTO RENEW. There are a ton of areas on GD.com where you CAN'T shut off auto-renew, and apparently ONE where you can, or can't you? On a computer & the product checked I click on "auto renew ON" because no icon says either "auto renew OFF" or simply "auto renew." The ONLY other option is carefully titled "Cancel Renewal" lol no joke, so everyones naturally freaked out but you click & it brings up a warning box you're about to cancel your service! Do I click THAT to STOP auto-renew? How do I actually shut off auto-renew for domains and hosting?? HELP - with GD I am a deer in the woods about to be shot at all times!! Where else can I take my business where its not so slimy?

title: I used godaddy to make my own web page…
text: I used godaddy to make my own web page for a business I'm trying to start up. I designed my own page, as like anyone, I wanted my exact choice of layout and content. It took some time to do, which one reason was because I was only allowed to upload pictures of 30mb or belown, and the files I needed to upload from my stockers sites were larger than 30mb, therefore they could not be up loaded. So it was a long process for me of screen shot, copy, paste for upload. The time scale was nearly a month to produce my still not finished website, and when the trial design expired, godaddy then prompt either buy to continue the site build or basically scrap it all and start again. I called godaddy to discuss what happens once I buy it ect and was explained by the gentleman on the line what the cost was covering and he did say that I could activate it whilst working on it still, and once I was ready to buy the page, to email him and he would see about discount for a new customer. So a week or so after the call, I emailed the man to say I'm ready to proceed. I heard nothing back over a long period of time, so thought I'll call again and see whats happening? I spoke to a differnet person this time, and 1st I asked why I can't find my designed page any longer? After some searching, he came back to say that the page had been permanently deleted. I could not believe all my time and effort had been for nothing and my business website further delayed. I asked why it was deleted, he replied that after a certain time of the trial ending, if not purchased, deletion. I was not told this by the previous member of staff. I was then offered to have the page built for me and that a builder would contact me and go through the creation and then once built I could view the site and once happy purchase it. I was told 10 days or less to build it and also offered a discount from £240 down to £200. All of this seemed like the best possible rectification for having deleted my own made site due to miss communication. Once again I was asked to email when I had all my pictures and info ready, and then once I email, a web builder will then be in contact. nearly 2 weeks and 2 emails later, yet again I hear nothing and have to call. This time I spoke with a lady, who was very polite, but after much explaining and going over the same thing she finally understood why I was calling and on numerous occasions put me on hold to go off and find things out and or ask, I assume, what she needs to do with my particular call as it took an hour just in the end to ask a couple of questions about what I wanted on my site, and the cost, which was either £167 incl vat or £167 plus vat, this was not really cleared up. But the cost was not my concern at this point, andI was still prepared to pay in full, but I was not expected after all the aboves events, to then be asked to pay in full for my page to be designed. I refused to pay and said that the page needs to be designed 1st before I pay anything, especially as I had been so messed about already, the least that could be done by godaddy is design 1st and take payment after. The lady said her hands were tied and despite my asking for a manager to make the decision, this to was not attempted and the call ended with me saying if no one can over rule me having to pay upfront then I won't bother with the site at all. No trying to keep my custom, or want to make right the 2 members of staff not replying to a customerthat they said they would. I had to call and chase,and lets not forget my page being deleted because their member of staff didn't explain things properly. instead months of my time wasted and not a sorry or rectification in sight.  If it were my company that put a customer through all of this, I would make sure everything was put right, and the customer well looked after. Notexpect them to pay in advance, when the free service has failed so bad.  Who would pay upfront for a website to be made after my experience?

title: Somehow my public_html folder disappeared
text: Somehow my public_html folder disappeared today. I could not determine what happened, but only that there was still 25GB of data usage showing for my site which was hosting multiple domains. Finally, after being on the phone and chat sessions for 6 hours today, I was able, this evening, to speak with Jose Lorenzo at GoDaddy about the problem, and he was able to resolve the issue in less than eight minutes. He found that my public_html folder had somehow been moved into my SSL folder. Jose's brilliance and gift for troubleshooting the problem was so greatly impressive and appreciated. His reassurance and kindly disposition makes him exceptional in light of the fact that I have multiple companies hosted on my server, and I was going to be facing the alligators if all of these were found to be not working in the morning. Nevertheless, I can now get a few hours of sleep, and at sunrise my colleagues will not know of the great disappearance event. But, thank you and God bless you Jose Lorenzo at GoDaddy Hosting Support for resolving my issue. In summary, I learned from Jose that if your site statistics show 25GB of data usage, and you don’t have a public_html folder showing, or the one you have is empty, look for your files under another folder, as was my case, the SSL folder. How did my folder get moved? I do not know, unless by hand twitch or computer glitch it was dragged down without my awareness of the move. But, it was found and restored to its appropriate location by Jose and all is well.

title: Updated review - Interactions started off badly but now reached a resolution
text: UPDATE:  Following this review I was contacted directly over email by Jaq who was extremely efficient, understanding, and was able to resolve everything completely. The first experience with customer support was terrible, but Jaq's support more than made up for everything. I'm happy with the resolution of the full refund and impressed at how swiftly Jaq dealt with everything internally as well. Admittedly it shouldn't have had to come to this, but no company is perfect and what really matters is how a company resolves things when everything doesn't go smoothly. Jaq is an asset to GoDaddy and has made up for the first experience. Thanks Jaq ------------------ Spoke to Nongam and Sagan on Live Chat and they are refusing to refund an auto renewal for an unused domain which was not authorised to be charged to my card, when I am cancelling well within my 14 day statutory right as a UK consumer. Their own contract states that as a UK consumer I have 14 days to cancel products and services ordered from GoDaddy, yet they are insisting that a refund is not possible.  As per the Consumer Contracts Regulations 2013, clauses 29, 30, 31 and 32, they are currently breaking UK law by refusing to honour my statutory right to 14 day cancellation as a UK customer. Trustpilot, please investigate this, consumers need to be protected from this horrific level of illegal malpractice.  And if you're thinking of getting a domain from GoDaddy, stay WELL clear. They will keep your card details on file and extract money from you years down the line against your will, then refuse to pay it back when no services have been provided. Absolutely disgusting.

title: AMAZING customer service. Thank you Jezrell <3
text: Anything to do with computers can be insanely frustrating... its usually user error... we don't quite know what we're doing, we aren't professionals, and we don't want to shell out the $$ to have someone else do what seems like a simple task for us. Then, we get annoyed. Customer service agents deal with cranky, frustrated, non-tech-savvy folks all day, and lets be honest, we aren't always polite.. by the time we get to the point where we need to call for help, we're usually not in the best mood.  Twice now, I've needed to call an agent from GoDaddy and both occasions really blew my socks off. Such wonderful client care, patience, I wound up laughing and smiling, instead of throwing my laptop off of my balcony... which was a real possibility. I don't know much about the company, the website templates are very basic... it's not necessarily a high quality platform.. but the price is right, for a basic landing page, which is why I've used the service to set up basic websites for a couple of friends. Honestly though, I know that when i run into an issue, I'm not going to end up pulling my hair out over tech support, because the service is UNREAL. Today I dealt with "Jezrell".. and I really wish I could recall the last agents name because he was an ALLSTAR too. (Even down to getting my cell number and calling to check in on my site progress, and helping me get a great discount) I'm not one to write a review in most cases (too lazy).. but the customer service staff at GoDaddy truly deserve some acknowledgement.

title: Shameful company and shameful client…
text: Shameful company and shameful client care. We were asked by the “payment verification” team to upload ID, bank statements, and photos of our debit card to prove that it was us who made the £1 domain name payment. Did this, and were told everything was hunky dory. About 10 minutes later the site disappeared. To cut a long story short, it turns out they absolutely love clients who operate fraudulent websites (backhanders, anyone?), but are not so welcoming to clients whose purpose is to offer a fraud prevention service, as we do, Oh yes, forgot, they steal your domain name as well. Avoid these dirty scammers at all cost. UPDATE So these dirty scammers have now replied with their fits- all copy-and-paste replies asking for “further information”. Bottom line: if you did provide this “further information”, they won’t respond - AGAIN. Why? Because the only purpose of GoDaddy is to steal your domain and then sell it on the open market.  Oh yes, one more thing: after providing them with ID and debit card details as per their bogus  “payment verification” team, our credit card started lighting up all over the world like a Christmas tree. So they’re identity thieves as well UPDATE Nr 2 Just received a reply a reply from GoDaddy telling us to f.u.c.k off. UPDATE Nr 3 GoDaddy STOLE the domain name we paid for and has NO intention of either refunding us or allowing us to transfer it to another registrar. UPDATE Nr 4 Still no sign of our refund; in the meantime one or more employees of GoDaddy appear to have used our debit card to do their Christmas shopping UPDATE Nr 5 Still no reply received NOR a refund appearing in our bank account. Meanwhile, someone within GoDaddy U.K. used our debit card to do their Christmas shopping. Scandalous. UPDATE Nr 6 Fraudsters GoDaddy steal your domain name and identity. Stay well clear. UPDATE Nr 7 Despite the fake “copied-and-pasted” reply Godaddy send to all their scammed customers, not a single reply to our numerous emails has been received.  It’s safe to assume that every single 5 star review on this site has been purchased by these fraudster. No refund received to date for the domain they stole from us, and our debit card used by Godaddy to make their Christmas purchases. Disgusting dirty scammers. UPDATE Nr 8 Still no refund from these dirty scammers and no replies to my emails. The identity theft by Godaddy has now been reported to the Police UPDATE Nr 9 GoDaddy stills your credit card details. Stay well away

title: Godaddy has gotten worse over time
text: Update:  I thought my comment was annonymous. But TrustPilot went ahead and shared my email address with Godaddy. I feel incredibly violated. Such a betrayal of trust. I wonder if TrustPilot is owned by Godaddy and not telling us. If that's the case, I would've never left a comment. And if it's not, it should inform us it shares our information and email address with Godaddy. Beware you commenters. We can't trust TrustPilot.  Now I have to worry about Godaddy terminating my account because I vented off and told a whole bunch of truth I knew they obviously wouldn't accept as truth and put out their own fake truth. I've been a customer of Godaddy for 21 years! YES. A LONG TWENTY ONE YEARS. That means I know what I'm talking about. It used to take only seconds, if not just minutes, to get someone on the phone. Plus, everyone was in the U.S. Now, 8 out of 10 times we're placed on hold with hold time over one hour no matter what time of the day or night we're calling, and then calls are routed to someone in the Philippines who can't even help us or maybe they can. So, getting service is a hit or miss.  I KNOW all that because I've been doing this for 21 years. You can't come tell us things are the same. That's just not true.  Godaddy deleted up to 100,000 of my emails, too, back in 2017. Those were emails from 2001-2011, spanning ten long years. They were ALL business emails. They said nothing to me until I found out accidentally two months later. I found out that happened to hundreds, if not thousands, of others too. I couldn't sue Godaddy because we have to show "actual monetary damage." That was a horrible and depressing experience. Terrible. Terrible. Horrible. Need I say more? It still makes me angry even thinking about it. Godaddy never made it up to me and never sent me one word of apology either. NONE. I had to find out on my own that the "log files" had been deleted, either intentionally or inadvertently, Who knows? Who's there to tell the truth? Something happened there. We don't know what, but we can guess. Regardless, I personally think it could've been ecause Godaddy wanted to save money on server expense. Is that true? I have no idea. Everything I say would be speculation. It could've been that their IT team we never have access to made a colossal mistake. But one thing is clear: Godaddy should've known it happened. And Godaddy doesn't EVER communicate with its customers about anything except just a handful of times all these years! That's nothing at all. If anything goes wrong, the Terms of the agreement says we are on our own.  One more thing happening in the past year: Godaddy intentionally changes the settings to "auto renew." it's done it twice without my permission. It takes a lot of work to undo it. That's just not right not matter what standard you're using. The choice should be ours.    Also, I know for a fact WorkSpace was far more superior to this ridiculous MS 365 email service and it was just as safe. So, please don't tell us MS365 is better. In fact, Microsoft doesn't provide phone suppoer any more. Shame on Bill Gates and Microsoft that with hundreds of billions of dollars in cash alone they have cut out all live services. And since Godaddy tells me I have to call Microsoft, that does nothing to help me and everything to anger us.  Really?! I guess we don't have brains! It's best for you to be honest about things and stop playing coporate games of telling us all that Godaddy does its best! If this is its best, though, obviously that's not good enough. Having said everything above. I appreciate any and all great service I do get when I do get it. I thought I have to be fair here.  Correction: I wrote erroneously that some of my emails hadn't been transferred. That was an error. Sorry about that. It is some of my email addresses that haven't been transferred. I know because they're not there. So, please don't come back telling me everything is OK.   Original Comment:  Godaddy has gotten worse over time. It retired its great email software "WorkSpace" and switched to Microsoft 365 Outlook telling everyone it's because of security holes. That's B.S. and false. MS 365 Outlook has issues. Not all my emails were transferred. Emails scheduled for future delivery don't have their own folder; they are kept inside "Drafts" folder, making it extremely difficult to find them, whereas WorkSpace had a folder designed for scheduled emails. Godaddy should have and could have improved the security of WorkSpace. It didn't have any security-related reasons to make the switch and put us through hell and start charging more money too.  Also, Godaddy has terminated a ton of its tech support staff and outsourced it to the Philippines just to save money. Nowadays, it could take more than one hour to get someone on the phone, that is if we are lucky. So, 8 out of 10 times that's what happens.

title: False Advertisement, argumentative support.
text: I spotted on GoDaddy’s UK website you can sync Facebook and GoDaddy online stores.  After purchasing the e-commerce website and setting it up, I was not able to achieve the above. Support couldn’t figure this out, escalated the issue to senior technical support and they got back to me in 72 hours.  They stated this feature was not available in the UK, I couldn’t respond to this as they closed the case before I was able to respond.  I contacted support again and requested a refund, they refused this request as it had been past the 48 hour window, I tried to argue my case but they wouldn’t listen.  I then asked to escalate the issue for formal complaint, they would not do this and simply stated they would “discuss with their team”.  I haven’t mentioned that although the support representative was understanding, they were also argumentative. Even after I sent the link to the guide that clearly states this option is available in the UK, plus it is on the UK.GoDaddy site, they were adamant the issue wasn’t with them and it wasn’t their fault as the feature “wasn’t available in my region”.  I tried stating it was false advertisement, I was unhappy with support, I wanted to to escalate the issue to someone senior in customer service, Nothing worked. They were simply trying to butter me up and do sod all.  First Trustpilot review I’ve ever written, I’ve had bad experiences before but never one like this where I’ve wanted to stop others falling into the same trap.

title: Malicious business practices
text: So three/four years back. I do not remember the time exactly, I wanted to get a .com domain of my name and wanted to host my blog. So I searched my name twice or thrice on GoDaddy and also looked for other options like hosting and all. I just completed my college and got into a low paying job so budget was an issue. I loved the prices listed on go Daddy. Now here comes a twist. While I was budgeting up to get a domain and hosting, I found out that the domain with my name is taken. Whois records tell it's booked by GoDaddy. The webpage it serves is a page of GoDaddy advertisement that says domain is available on GoDaddy for sale. I try to get it from them and it says it will require a brokerage fee for negotiation and post negotiation it will require buying cost additional. The brokerage cost was 60 times the cost they were listing the domain for and I do not want to think about how much they would have asked for domain itself. Now I added a Google Calendar entry to get my domain when it gets expired and I got a temporary domain for myself till that time. Next year searched the domain name once  again in their whois because the price they offer is is excellent. Atleast half, if not just 5% the cost told by other registrars. And within 24 hours the domain is booked for an year more. I searched and got to know that if the domain I wanted to get, gets a single ping they will try to hold it and try to bargain on their terms. So for next time I did a whois on ICANN official and it told me exact period the domain will be available. I waited for the period and grace period to be expire. Then the very next day I booked my domain with Google for full 10 years. I got to know that if I would have gone with GoDaddy, I would have paid 1.5+ times the price I paid for Google for 10 years. Only first year the charge less for a domain. From next year they charge comparatively more.  In summary, GoDaddy wanted me to pay GoDaddy for a brokerage of domain held by GoDaddy. So that GoDaddy negotiate a price to be paid to GoDaddy from me to get me a domain on GoDaddy. This long one is just out of frustration which is nearly hate for them. Try some good Registation services and try to avoid them.

I thought about not writing this review and just sitting on the cost, but after realizing that GoDaddy used my 4 inactive domains to cover it with their GoDaddy ads & call to actions to 'register your domain', while I was sitting/paying them to host their Ad for almost 1+ year now ... I thought it was a great fit to share my experience. There are other providers out there that act 100x more friendly and forthcoming about what they have to offer. I'll be moving away from GoDaddy.

title: GoDaddy product experience has gone…
text: GoDaddy product experience has gone downhill.  In an effort to dumb things down for users who know nothing about managing hosting and domains, they have added like 15 more steps to do things then there were before (I may be exaggerating).  When adding domains to Managed Wordpress Sites, I often have to remove and reconnect them because it doesn't work properly the first time.  There was an option to clone a MWP site, it did not work.  When trying to manage DNS records, it has can't edit, can't delete when I cancelled any products it would have been tied to.  Chat support goes to India which goes against everything GoDaddy stood for keeping US support in the US.  The people in India have no idea what they are doing.  So once I wasted 15 minutes in chat of them saying they can't transfer to the US, I'm currently on hold for basic DNS support on why there is an issue where I can't edit the DNS on my domain and I've currently been on hold for over 20 minutes with no answer yet.  Wait times definitely longer than what I am used to.  Maybe the GoDaddy Pro experience should be formatted differently. Started chat at 1:15 pm, started phone call at about 1:30, took 40 minutes for a rep to be on the line.  I don't think GoDaddy should ever "lock" the DNS regardless if it is connected to a product in the account.  The system glitches (which have become more frequent) stop people from being able to manage their own domain. title: GoDaddy Technical Support Keep Destroying Live Website
text: Yet again GoDaddy Technical support messed up my website when I called in for support. The call was raised because despite no changes having been made to my site, the appointment booking facility failed. Clearly an issue with a GoDaddy update. This time the call was initially handled better than previously as the customer service representative actually listened and didn't try to fix the issue himself. He escalated the problem to Level 2 Technical support in the Barcelona office. In view of my previous experiences where staff have fiddled with my website and changed the settings or removed elements without my permission, I gave strict instructions that NO staff were allowed to make ANY changes to my website.  The only permission granted was to view my website and then to provide instructions for me to fix it. I repeated these instructions four times in case there was any language comprehension issues (as there had been previously since many of the staff are Spanish).  The customer service representative was very clear with his understanding of these instructions and apologised for the previous issues I had experienced. So feeling confident I could trust GoDaddy not to make changes to my website, I left the issue with them. With a few hours I checked on my site and saw that not only had someone in Level 2 Technical support completely ignored my instructions, but that the colours of my website had been changed and, even more serious, the title of one of the sections had been changed (I refer to this section by name throughout the website so customers would no longer be able to find it). I am outraged that no one at GoDaddy appears to respect customers' wishes.  I am disappointed that I had to correct the edits myself. I am frustrated that the history of changes saved by GoDaddy does not show what has been changed so I am left not knowing what has been removed, edited, updated on my site and what may still be incorrect. Why is it so hard to carry out customer's wishes GoDaddy? I am an experienced GoDaddy website builder - many of the staff have commented on how professional the site looks like and that it is one of the best they have seen. When I tell GoDaddy that I am capable of making any edits needed as a result of a GoDaddy software update, I am capable! I do not want my wishes to be ignored any more and am seriously considering leaving GoDaddy and having my website built by a developer which would mean I was no longer in fear that my website was going to be wrecked by incompetent GoDaddy technical staff who need to fiddle with someone's website to get the result, rather than having the expertise required to understand the issue without dabbling with someone's live website. I would like a response as I'm so fed up with having to raise the same issue again and again and again. This must be the 8th time that someone at GoDaddy has changed my website without my permission. That is a shocking catalogue of repeated errors. Worse, I phoned in to report this issue and was asked to send an email detailing the issue. I stayed on the phone to ensure that the email had been received and waited until it had been forwarded to the relevant department. However, no one has bothered to reply.... I think that shows what GoDaddy are like.

title: Impossible to file a complaint
text: We took a lot of time an effort to research which provider would be the best to set up our e-commerce website with. Reading the great comments about GoDaddy and their amazing customer service where you can actually speak to someone sounded ideal so we went for it. As long as you don't have a complaint to file the customer service team is helpful. Although you are given different advice from each team member. If you want to buy a product from them they are excellent. Sadly this is not the case when you are not happy with something. There is literally no option when you call them. When you send a chat they divert you to call the customer support team who is not able to transfer you to anyone who can listen to your issue and address it. They offer a call back that suits them and if you miss the call, though. They will email you ... apparently.  I was advised that for the UK there is only one person who deals with complaints. SHOCKING!  I spent hours and hours of trying to find out what the complaints procedure is and I still don't know. I spoke to different people all advising different things.  If you are considering GoDaddy I would urge you to reconsider.

text: Overall: Great customer service. Voice was clear and directions were very easy to understand. I was always told what was happening on their end and felt very supported. They were also very patient when waiting for me to do things on my end. I know sometimes customer service calls can feel very stiff and too professional but during our wait we were able to have a few casual words that helped me feel like I was actually talking to a person. My issue: My expired domains were only able to be renewed WITH the "Ultimate Protection Plan". Deleting one from my cart also deleted my renewal order. But trying to downgrade my protection plan told me I was already at the lowest option. Weird. Solution: I needed to renew domains WITH the plans first so they weren't expired, then the representative gave me a refund for the plans after. This involved getting an email and telling them a specific code over the phone to validate the refund.

title: Tech Problem led to More Solutions!
text: I was having difficulty setting up my business email because I had purchased my domain through GoDaddy's 3rd party vendor.  I called customer service after trying the chat option and was connected to a gentleman I'll refer to as W.  W was friendly, knowledgeable, and helped me immediately.  I especially appreciated the acknowledgement that what I was trying to do was more complicated than normal, and I didn't feel stupid for not being able to complete the task on my own.  While waiting for the team to work in the background, W talked with me about other startup business experiences he's been exposed to (no confidential details, just big picture stuff).  Not only did he help bolster my confidence as I go through a bout of new business jitters, he was also able to connect me with a much-needed service through GoDaddy that I didn't know was available. I am much less intimidated by the website experience knowing that I have customer support like W behind me!

title: Website editor down for all users
text: Website editor is down for all users, and has been so for ~4 hours now. Their status page says all working fine, but customer service have literally confirmed a server-wide issue which affects all users. Agent advised that there is no way for me to see when it is working again so I just have to 'keep trying' and it might work at some point. He has offered to email me when it is working again, but cannot promise because he has other calls to support. If I call back in once the issue has been resolved then I might get one day of service credited back to my account for the inconvenience. If this is the (sometimes working) service that you want for your business, GoDaddy is for you.

title: Frustrations, with excellent customer service follow up after making a complaint.
text: Update: following my review I was contacted via email by Anna. I provided her with a detailed account of my frustrations, along with copies of the live chat history. She has looked into the issues I’ve had and has provided me with a solution for which I’m very grateful. The social media tweaks seem to have finished (it was a known back-end problem which some chat agents were not aware of) this morning and I am now able to post via GoDaddy again. I have suggested that for known problems customers are informed via email to prevent frustrations, and I hope that this has been taken on board. Originally 2 stars, now upgraded to 4. Provided I have no further issues I would continue to recommend GoDaddy to other business owners. Original review: GoDaddy has continually tweaked their websites+ecommerce marketing dashboards. Since their last 'update' the social media feed onto my dashboard does not work. I have spent over 4.5hrs on live chat trying to get them to fix it. It was left with - 'our tech team will rebuild and I will email you when it is fixed' - now over 8 weeks and nothing. During that interaction I was promised a good discount on renewal - when I asked I was given a pittance and found a code on search which gave me more of a discount. Today, another 'tweak'. The dashboard is now not loading properly. I cannot run an e-commerce website if you cannot provide me with a functioning platform.
